# 1. 新たな依頼は……

Airi: Okay, so... Our next meeting is Wednesday night, and we have that interview on Saturday...
Airi: After that, we have a little bit of a gap...
Airi: Oh, hang on. I think they wanted to move this meeting to a different day.
Airi: *Sigh* I was about to schedule us for something else here. I need to not forget about stuff like this.
Airi: It's great that we've been receiving so many offers, but this is starting to become too much for just us to handle...
Airi: Shizuku's even been helping me with this lately, which has made things easier compared to before...
Airi: *Sigh* I can't give enough respect to people who manage idols. How do they do it...?
Airi: Huh? A message? Oh, it could be another offer...
Airi: F-For TV...?!
Airi: I couldn't be more grateful that people want us to appear. And it looks like they want us on for one of their segments. I wonder what it's about...
Airi: Hey, they want us to report on a cafe! I think that's a first for us.
Airi: I really wanna do this since I'm pretty good at this sort of stuff.
Airi: I gotta let the others know...!
Airi: Sorry I'm late! I hope I didn't keep you waiting... Huh?
Shizuku: Oh, Airi, hello.
Airi: Wait... Minori isn't here yet?
Haruka: No, she's on classroom duty today, so she'll be running a little late.
Shizuku: She sounded very excited. I remember her saying, “I'm gonna write the best log entry ever!”
Airi: Hehe. Looks like she's trying to get the most out of regular school life before she goes credit-based...
Airi: Anyway, I guess we can start discussing our next stream and...
Rin: Oh, Airi and the others are here!
MEIKO: Haruka told us the good news! You get to go on TV again, yes?
Miku: You're reporting on a cafe, right? What does that involve exactly?
Airi: It's a segment for a show called “The Late Nite Wednesday Talk Show”, and we get to introduce a cafe in Shibuya that's been getting a lot of buzz.
Airi: It's hosted by a popular idol and TV personality, and the show itself has been getting pretty good ratings.
Rin: Really? Then, this is a huge offer!
Shizuku: The show's producer was apparently looking for some high schoolers who knew Shibuya well, which led them to us.
Luka: The producer contacted you directly? This must've been a big decision.
Rin: It's proof that everyone in TV is talking about MORE MORE JUMP! now!
Haruka: Yes, that may be a part of it...
Haruka: But it's actually quite common for staff we have worked with before to refer us as guests for TV gigs.
Airi: Right. As a result, in terms of landing these appearances, who you know ends up being more important than how famous you are.
Airi: Either way, I'm really happy.
Len: So that's how it works.
KAITO: But I have to think the staff referred you girls because of all the hard work you've done up until now.
KAITO: I'm looking forward to seeing it air.
Airi: Yeah, of course! We'll bring over a video after it does!
Miku: Oh, this is so exciting♪
MEIKO: Do you know which cafe you'll be going to?
Haruka: No, they said they're still working out the details. We should receive word once everything's finalized.
Minori: Everyone! I have big news! No, huge news!
Shizuku: Oh, Minori, hello. I hope classroom duty went well.
Airi: What's going on? Why do you sound so flustered?
Haruka: Did something happen?
Minori: S-S-S-So... That cafe we're supposed to introduce...
Minori: They picked the one where I work!!!
Airi: What?!
Shizuku: Oh, what are the odds...?
Minori: But there's a bit of a problem...
Miku: A bit of a problem?
Minori: Yeah. During the day of the shoot, they're gonna be short on staff.
Haruka: Short on staff...?
Minori: A big group made a reservation on the same day as our shoot, which was okay since someone with years of experience had a shift scheduled.
Minori: But they can't make it now because of a family matter...
Minori: One person agreed to fill in, but we're afraid that it's gonna be too much for them...
Rin: Oh no. That's terrible...
Luka: And you can't help because of the shoot.
Minori: Exactly! Our hands are tied because I'm not available!
Minori: On top of all that, the manager's been wishing for the longest time that our cafe would get a TV spot. I was so happy at first when I heard the news...
Minori: But at this rate, the cafe won't be able to handle a TV shoot, let alone run properly. Which means they might have to turn down this offer...
Miku: Isn't there anything we can do...?
Len: Well... I'm sure the manager really wants to do this, so it might be good to tell the show's staff that.
Airi: Would it be possible for someone to work there just for a day?
Minori: Huh...?
Haruka: Do you know someone who can?
Airi: Yeah. I think I know just the person.
Airi: Not only do they work part-time as front-end staff for retail, they can do quite a lot. Cooking, prepping or waiting tables should be a cinch.
Airi: But there's no guarantee that they'll agree to help...
Minori: Please ask them! I'll let the manager know what's going on!
Airi: Hehe. Got it. Then, I'll try asking them.
